        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Takahiro Shi­raishi, 30, was sen­tenced to death on Tues­day for the mur­der of nine peo­ple in 2017. He used Twit­ter to lure eight sui­ci­dal women to his home in Zama, out­side Tokyo, where he drugged, robbed, raped and killed them be­fore he cut up their bod­ies in his 13.5 sq m apart­ment. The only man among the vic­tims was killed when he went to look for his miss­ing ac­quain­tance.</p>

